			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify;  background-color: #020A0F;   background-image: none;  background-repeat: repeat-x; " >
												I had the opportunity to log into test the other day and play around with the /melody command a little.  I have played my bard for just about 3 years now and after mashing keys for that long I am looking forward to this new command.<br>However, I would like to see a couple of changes.<br>1. Please make a level requirement or some restriction of that nature.  This command is really only useful in situations like trash mob clearing and farming.  When the shift hits the fan us bards need to have the knowledge of manual twisting in order to change our twist to deal with the situation.  Allowing a lowbie bard to have this command would allow someone to totally forget the important step in playing a bard.  I would set this level somewhere around 35 or 40.<br><br>2. Please, oh pwetty pwease, fix the casting bar.  When I was on test the casting bar would reappear everytime the song refreshed.  This was so blasted annoying I cannot find the words to express myself other than AAARRRRGGGGHHHHH!!!! yep I think that says it about right <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-very-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br><br>Other than those issues I am pleased with the progression of this idea.  Bard bots beware, you will have to pay just as much attention to your bot as a normal bard muwahahahaha.
																		
										</td></tr>
