									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 395 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_5.gif' border=0 alt='1 rating - 5.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Personally, I am very much looking forward to this.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I however, do feel that it should be an ability gained either at first level, or a low level, and here is my reasoning:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1.&nbsp; Social Activity: EQ is a social game.&nbsp; To be social, I need to talk to people. Now most social activities come through when your having down time. Most classes just sit for downtime, bards usually have to play songs.&nbsp;&nbsp; Now I know most people just put one song on and leave it that way, but really its mroe effective if you can twist more than one during downtime...of course, that keeps you from being social.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. Commuincation: Much like #1 above, you some times need to get a specific message to someone.&nbsp; If your busy twisting a mez, a damage sheild, and whatever other songs, you can't get the message through without stopping the twisting.&nbsp; /melody will help this a little.&nbsp;&nbsp; This is further important if the Bard happens to be the group or raid leader.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3.&nbsp; Ease of play: When I broke two of my fingers in a small accident at home, I was still able to play my shaman, my cleric, and my warrior.&nbsp; But I couldnt' effectively play my Bard.&nbsp; Of course, my hand got better.&nbsp; But there are some people who may have physical handicaps (or even carpal tunnel) and just can't twist the songs.&nbsp; Should these people be excluded just for this reason?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. Connection Speed: Alot of wether your could twist 4 songs was based on your computer's connection speed or just your computer speed in general.&nbsp; No matter what I do - I cannot twist 4 songs unless I turn off the luclin graphics.&nbsp; Much like #3, I don't feel people should be excluded from being effective at a class based soley on their connection speed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Overall, I don't think that adding this function will meld the bad bards into the good bards.&nbsp; Bad Bards will still be unable to switch between targets to twist songs and get different effects.&nbsp; Basically you'll be able to idenfity a bad bard even easier, since all they'll really do is just play their best 3-4 songs while they fight, leaving the adds for others to take care of.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Though - perhaps a fair compromise would be to allow players to add more songs to the melody with more levels gained.</DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<DIV>levels 1-15 you get 1 song&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>levels 15 - 30 you get 2</DIV>
<DIV>levels&nbsp; 30 - 45 you get 3</DIV>
<DIV>levels &nbsp;46+ gets the 4.</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>This way, they can try to twist more manually if they want, but still have the option of playing the melody during downtime.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Another option may be to turn melody into a combat ability.&nbsp;&nbsp; Since twisting songs in RL takes some endurance, maybe they can turn melody into a combat ability that costs endurance overtime.&nbsp; This would prevent bard bots because eventually they would run out of endurance, and would still encourage people to manually twist songs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
