			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Personally, I think the use of /melody should have nothing to do with merit or level.&nbsp; A merit-based skill or AA has to be something that adds power or a unique ability to the class.&nbsp; This command doesn't.&nbsp; It is a feature of the interface and nothing more.&nbsp; Basically any bard who plays the game is capable of mastering the concept of twisting and the /melody feature does nothing but automate that.&nbsp; That doesn't increase a bard's power.&nbsp; It only simplifies the tasks involved in playing it.&nbsp; Making it a merit-based thing makes no sense.</DIV>
																		
